      • compareTo

        public int compareTo(PassengerInfo other)
        Compare this PassengerInfo object and other PassengerInfo object. An PassengerInfo 'info1' is "smaller" than another 'info2' if info1's TicketAmount is smaller than info2's. If both have the same TicketAmount, then one with a larger id is considered as "smaller". When being sorted in an increasing order (using Arrays.sort), the smaller PassengerInfo object appears earlier than the larger one.
        Specified by:
        compareTo in interface java.lang.Comparable<PassengerInfo>
        Returns:
        Positive value if this is larger than other, negative if this is smaller than other, zero otherwise.
